<p>I am trying to pass-on values from a dropdown to the textarea. </p>  <p>The non-working code is:</p>  <pre><code>&lt;form name="f"&gt;     &lt;textarea id="change" name="change"&gt;&lt;/textarea&gt;     &lt;br/&gt;        &lt;input id="docname" name="docname" type="text" list="docs" /&gt;     &lt;datalist id="docs"&gt;         &lt;option value="data1"&gt;         &lt;option value="data2"&gt;         &lt;option value="data3"&gt;         &lt;option value="data4"&gt;         &lt;option value="data5"&gt;         &lt;option value="dta6"&gt;     &lt;/datalist&gt; &lt;/form&gt;  &lt;script type="text/javascript"&gt;     document.forms['f'].elements['docname'].onchange = function(){         document.getElementById("change").value += this.value + ', ';            document.forms['f'].elements['docname'].value = '';     };                  &lt;/script&gt; </code></pre>  <p>However if I use <code>Input</code> instead of <code>Textarea</code> the code works as intended.</p>  <p>The working code:</p>  <pre><code>&lt;form name="f"&gt;     &lt;input id="change" name="change" value=""&gt;     &lt;input id="docname" name="docname" type="text" list="docs" /&gt;     &lt;datalist id="docs"&gt;         &lt;option value="data1"&gt;         &lt;option value="data2"&gt;         &lt;option value="data3"&gt;         &lt;option value="data4"&gt;         &lt;option value="data5"&gt;         &lt;option value="dta6"&gt;     &lt;/datalist&gt; &lt;/form&gt;  &lt;script type="text/javascript"&gt;     document.forms['f'].elements['docname'].onchange = function(){         document.getElementById("change").value += this.value + ', ';            document.forms['f'].elements['docname'].value = '';     };                  &lt;/script&gt; </code></pre>  <p>How can I use <code>Textarea</code> in place of <code>Input</code> and make the code work. I need to use <code>textarea</code> as I need multiple lines of text.</p>  <p><strong>PS: I am trying to create this <a href="http://jsfiddle.net/sumitcbrty/7zqn6j3u/2/" rel="nofollow">http://jsfiddle.net/sumitcbrty/7zqn6j3u/2/</a> but just want textarea instead of using input field</strong></p>